# Docker Development Workflow

## Container Setup

The project uses Docker for development, testing, and production environments:

- **Development**: [docker/docker-compose.dev.yml](mdc:docker/docker-compose.dev.yml) - Hot reload with volume mounts
- **Testing**: [docker/docker-compose.test.yml](mdc:docker/docker-compose.test.yml) - Isolated test environment
- **Production**: [docker/docker-compose.prod.yml](mdc:docker/docker-compose.prod.yml) - Optimized production build

## Development Commands

Use the [Makefile](mdc:Makefile) for common operations:

- `make dev` - Start development environment with hot reload
- `make build` - Build the application
- `make test-all` - Run all tests in Docker
- `make test-unit` - Run unit tests only
- `make test-integration` - Run integration tests
- `make clean` - Clean up Docker resources
- `make clippy` - Run code quality checks
- `make fmt` - Format code

## Container Configuration

- Development container runs in privileged mode for system operations
- Uses host networking for easier debugging
- Mounts source code volumes for hot reload
- Caches Cargo dependencies in Docker volumes
- Health checks configured for monitoring

## Security Considerations

- Containers run as root inside (required for system operations)
- Uses Linux namespaces and cgroups for isolation
- Implements seccomp for system call filtering
- Validates all inputs before execution

## Environment Variables

- `RUST_LOG=debug` - Enable debug logging
- `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` - Enable backtraces for debugging
- `CARGO_HOME=/usr/local/cargo` - Cargo cache location
